Titolo: Sea Dragon (video game)

Anno: 1982

Descrizione: Sea Dragon is a horizontally scrolling shooter for the TRS-80 computer, written by Wayne Westmoreland and Terry Gilman, and released in 1982 by Adventure International. The gameplay is similar to the Scramble arcade game, but underwater. It was ported to the Apple II, Atari 8-bit family, Commodore 64, TRS-80 Color Computer, and IBM PC.
In 1995, Wayne Westmoreland placed the game into the public domain. In January 2016 the source code for the Atari 8-bit version was released to the public and added to the Internet Archive.